		<td><b>Bugged cart of Super Mario Bros? (music speed/demo glitches)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have a copy of Super Mario Bros. (PAL). When I play it on my NES two weird things happen: the speed of the music is like 1.5x as fast; the instruments even go out of sync when the time is almost up (when the music plays even faster). The demo, which shows up when you don't press any buttons at the Title Screen for a while, is all messed up. First Mario walks to the right, bumps into a pipe, then walks left and jumps, missing the '?'-box with the mushroom in it and moves back to the right, again jumping and missing. Then he jumps over the pipe, crashes into a Goomba and dies.
<br />Does someone knows what's going on? Is it rare? I can record a video and record the sound when you guys are interested.
<br /> -DvdHeijden

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


